# Arduino Radar System

## Description
This project is a simple radar system using an Arduino, ultrasonic sensor, and a servo motor to detect objects in a sweep motion.

## Components
- Arduino Uno/Nano
- HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor
- Servo motor
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard

## Wiring
- HC-SR04 Trigger → Arduino pin 9
- HC-SR04 Echo → Arduino pin 10
- Servo PWM → Arduino pin 6
- Power and GND connections accordingly

## How to Run
1. Open `src/ArduinoRadar.ino` in Arduino IDE
2. Install [NewPing library](https://github.com/microflo/NewPing)
3. Upload code to Arduino
4. Open Serial Monitor to view distances
5. Watch the servo sweep objects

